## Select variables of interest - here just looking at the winds so saving wind and time variables
included_cols = ['day','hour_UTC','wdir','wspd_m_per_s','wspdmax_m_per_s','year','month'] 

## convert to a numpy array for model input and only include included_cols in the dataframe
data = df.loc[:, df.columns.isin(list(included_cols))]

## check the shape of your data
print(f'Your data shape is: {np.shape(data)}')
print(data.shape)

In [5]:
### fill in missing data using simple methods available in pandas
df_nomissing=data.copy()
df_nomissing=df_nomissing.fillna(method='bfill')
df_nomissing=df_nomissing.fillna(method='ffill')
In [6]:
## convert wind from meters per second to miles per hour
convert=1

if convert==1:
    df_nomissing['wspd_m_per_s']=(df_nomissing.wspd_m_per_s.values * units('mps')).to('mph')
    df_nomissing['wspdmax_m_per_s']=(df_nomissing.wspdmax_m_per_s.values * units('mps')).to('mph')
    df_nomissing.rename(columns={'wspd_m_per_s': 'wspd_mph'}, inplace=True)
    df_nomissing.rename(columns={'wspdmax_m_per_s': 'wspdmax_mph'}, inplace=True)
